---

# Backend Setup

```bash
cd notification_app_be

npm install

node server.js
```

Backend runs on:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

---

# Frontend Setup

```bash
cd notification_app_fe

npm install

npm run dev
```

Frontend runs on:

```text
http://localhost:5173
```

---

# API Endpoints

## Get Notifications

```http
GET /notifications
```

### Query Parameters

| Parameter | Description |
|---|---|
| page | Pagination page |
| limit | Number of notifications |
| notification_type | Filter by notification type |

Example:

```http
GET /notifications?page=1&limit=10&notification_type=Placement
```

---

# Logging Middleware

The application includes logging middleware which logs:
- request method
- request route
- backend events
- error events

